"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Agent-Contributed Custom Checkpoint Files (Cursor Chat Export)\n\n## Context\n\nWhen Cursor creates a checkpoint, we want to also include a cursor-chat export archive (`.cursor-chat.json`) in the checkpoint metadata. This is agent-specific data — other agents don't have Cursor's `store.db`. We need a simple extensibility point so any agent can contribute custom files to checkpoints in the future.\n\n## Approach: `CheckpointContributor` Optional Interface\n\nThe simplest approach with zero changes to the strategy layer:\n\n1. Define a new optional agent interface `CheckpointContributor` with one method\n2. Implement it on `CursorAgent` — it runs the cursor-export logic and writes the file to the session metadata dir\n3. Call it in `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` before `strat.SaveStep()` — the existing `addDirectoryToChanges()` in the checkpoint layer automatically picks up any file in the metadata dir\n\n**Why this works with no strategy changes:** The metadata directory (`sessionDirAbs`) is already recursively walked by `addDirectoryToChanges()` in `checkpoint/temporary.go:753`. Any file written there before `SaveStep()` is automatically included in the checkpoint tree. Same for condensation — `copyMetadataDir()` copies everything.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` | Add `CheckpointContributor` interface |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/checkpoint.go` | **Create** — implement `CheckpointContributor` for Cursor |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` | Add 5 lines to call `ContributeCheckpointFiles` before `SaveStep` |\n| `cmd/entire/cli/cursor_export.go` | Extract `exportCursorChat(ctx, agentID) ([]byte, error)` from `runCursorExport` |\n\n## Step 1: Add `CheckpointContributor` interface\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`\n\n```go\n// CheckpointContributor is an optional interface for agents that contribute\n// custom files to checkpoint metadata. Files are written to the session\n// metadata directory and automatically included in the checkpoint tree.\ntype CheckpointContributor interface {\n\t// ContributeCheckpointFiles writes agent-specific files to metadataDir.\n\t// Called before SaveStep; any files written are automatically included.\n\t// Errors are non-fatal (logged as warnings, checkpoint still proceeds).\n\tContributeCheckpointFiles(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, metadataDir string) error\n}\n```\n\nThat's it — one method, simple contract: write your files to `metadataDir`, they get included.\n\n## Step 2: Refactor `cursor_export.go` — extract reusable export function\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/cursor_export.go`\n\nExtract the core export logic out of `runCursorExport` into a function that doesn't need a `cobra.Command`:\n\n```go\n// exportCursorChatArchive exports a Cursor chat session as a JSON archive.\n// Returns the marshaled archive bytes. agentID is the Cursor conversation UUID.\nfunc exportCursorChatArchive(ctx context.Context, agentID string) ([]byte, error) {\n    // Same logic as runCursorExport but returns []byte instead of writing to file\n    // Uses existing findCursorFile, exportCursorDB, readCursorTranscript\n}\n```\n\nThe `runCursorExport` command handler becomes a thin wrapper that calls this and writes to disk.\n\n## Step 3: Implement on CursorAgent\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/checkpoint.go` (new)\n\n```go\n// ContributeCheckpointFiles exports the Cursor chat store.db as a\n// .cursor-chat.json archive into the checkpoint metadata directory.\nfunc (c *CursorAgent) ContributeCheckpointFiles(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, metadataDir string) error {\n    data, err := cli.ExportCursorChatArchive(ctx, sessionID)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(metadataDir, sessionID+\".cursor-chat.json\"), data, 0o600)\n}\n```\n\n**Import cycle concern:** The cursor agent package can't import the `cli` package directly. Two options:\n- **(a)** Move `exportCursorChatArchive` into a shared package (e.g., `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/chatexport/`)\n- **(b)** Move the export logic into the cursor agent package itself (it only uses `database/sql` + `encoding/json` + `filepath.Glob` — no `cli` dependency)\n\n**Option (b) is simpler** — the export logic is self-contained (SQLite read + JSON marshal). Move the core functions (`findCursorFile`, `exportCursorDB`, `readCursorTranscript`, archive types) into `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/chatexport.go`. The CLI command in `cursor_export.go` calls into it.\n\n## Step 4: Call in lifecycle.go\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`, in `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`, right before `strat.SaveStep()` (around line 375):\n\n```go\n// Let agent contribute custom files to the checkpoint metadata\nif contributor, ok := ag.(agent.CheckpointContributor); ok {\n    if err := contributor.ContributeCheckpointFiles(ctx, event.SessionID, sessionDirAbs); err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Warning: agent checkpoint contribution failed: %v\\n\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNon-fatal — if the export fails (e.g., no store.db found), the checkpoint still proceeds normally.\n\n## File Layout After Changes\n\n```\ncmd/entire/cli/agent/\n  agent.go                      # + CheckpointContributor interface (5 lines)\n  cursor/\n    checkpoint.go               # NEW — implements ContributeCheckpointFiles\n    chatexport.go               # NEW — cursor chat export logic (moved from cli package)\n    ...\ncmd/entire/cli/\n  cursor_export.go              # CLI command — thin wrapper calling cursor/chatexport\n  cursor_import.go              # Unchanged\n  lifecycle.go                  # + 5 lines calling CheckpointContributor\n```\n\n## What This Enables for Future Agents\n\nAny agent can implement `CheckpointContributor`:\n- **Claude Code**: Could export Claude's conversation cache\n- **Gemini CLI**: Could export Gemini session state\n- **OpenCode**: Could export its session metadata\n\nEach agent writes whatever files it wants to `metadataDir`. The framework doesn't need to know what those files are.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n# Manual test: trigger a Cursor checkpoint and verify .cursor-chat.json appears in the shadow branch tree\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/projects/-Users-gtrrz-victor-wks-cli-cli/f5d5ee18-4bb5-41ad-bc48-3375f441c0e8.jsonl\n\n---\n\nit does not create custom files into the checkpoint at entire/checkpoint/v1 branch when the checkpoint commit is being created. why ?"